text: Are you ready to join WLC's Class of 2024? Submit your deposit today to ensure a spot in the top-ranked residence halls in Wisconsin (according to Niche.com).
Wisconsin Lutheran College ranks 12th among colleges in the Midwest on the 2020 U.S. News & World Report "Best Value Schools" list.
Through Wisconsin Lutheran College's partnerships with several colleges and universities in a variety of academic programs, students have the chance to earn two degrees in less time.
We invite you to discover the Wisconsin Lutheran College experience, and there's no better way than by visiting campus. Schedule a personal tour today!

At WLC, we'll provide you with an academic and faith experience that will prepare you to see your purpose in everyday life and work. You'll discover your WHY so you can lead in ways that are powerful and world changing.
Are you ready to begin your journey to college? Our free, secure, online applications make it easy to apply to Wisconsin Lutheran College. Apply today!

Students Study Abroad During J Term
Students Study Abroad During J Term
WLC Students Travel Abroad with Professors

During J Term, Wisconsin Lutheran College students are traveling abroad to study in Italy and Zambia, accompanied by their professors. Both groups departed from Wisconsin Lutheran College on January 2, 2020.
Students and professors will be sharing their photos and experiences during their journeys. Check the Study Abroad section of the

The 12 students who are enrolled in WLC's "Virtues and Vices" English course are touring Italy with Dr. Martin Moldenhauer. Follow the trip as the students learn about the literature, art, architecture, culture, people, and customs of Italy. The group will visit Rome, Florence, Assisi, Orvieto, Siena, and Civita di Bagnoregio.

As part of their curriculum, WLC nursing students travel to Zambia during their junior year to study the implementation of health care programs across the globe. While there, they observe medical practices and procedures in local clinics and hospitals, learn about diverse cultures, and conduct health education programs. Follow the experiences of the 28 nursing students as they travel through Zambia with Dr. Sheryl Scott and four additional chaperones.

The goal of our arts programming at Wisconsin Lutheran College is to provide enriching arts experiences and  to improve the quality of life for all with live arts performances. We hope to see you at  many college and professional performing arts events this season!
The Center for Arts and Performance is located at 8815 W. Wisconsin Avenue. Free parking is available in the Parking Center, 8701 W. Wisconsin Avenue for many fine arts events.
